#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.200"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.200:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.200:0.2"
msgid "20. Brāhmaṇavagga"
msgstr "20. Brahmins"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.200:0.3"
msgid "200. Nissāraṇīyasutta"
msgstr "200. Elements of Escape"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.200:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimā, bhikkhave, nissāraṇīyā dhātuyo."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five elements of escape."

msgctxt "an5.200:1.2"
msgid "Katamā pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

# See BB’s note for vimuccati vs. adhimuccati, and compare AN 4.178.
#. VAR: kāmaṃ → kāme (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.200:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kāmaṃ manasikaroto kāmesu cittaṃ na pakkhandati "
"nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take a case where a mendicant focuses on sensual pleasures, but their mind "
"isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about them."

msgctxt "an5.200:1.4"
msgid ""
"Nekkhammaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"But when they focus on renunciation, their mind is eager, confident, "
"settled, and decided about it."

# I disagree with BB that sugata here means “well departed”. The term is used in lots of places, and the suffix never has a “gone” meaning. It just means “in a good state”.
#. VAR: sugataṃ → sukataṃ (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: suvisaṃyuttaṃ → visaṃyuttaṃ (katthaci)
msgctxt "an5.200:1.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ "
"kāmehi;"
msgstr ""
"Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and "
"well detached from sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "an5.200:1.6"
msgid ""
"ye ca kāmapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so taṃ "
"vedanaṃ vediyati."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of sensual pleasures, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "an5.200:1.7"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ kāmānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. (1)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from sensual pleasures is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.200:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno byāpādaṃ manasikaroto byāpāde cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focuses on ill will, but their mind isn’"
"t eager …"

msgctxt "an5.200:2.2"
msgid ""
"Abyāpādaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto abyāpāde cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on good will, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "an5.200:2.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ "
"byāpādena;"
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from ill will."

msgctxt "an5.200:2.4"
msgid ""
"ye ca byāpādapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of ill will, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "an5.200:2.5"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ. (2)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from ill will is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.200:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno vihesaṃ manasikaroto vihesāya cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focuses on harming, but their mind isn’t "
"eager …"

msgctxt "an5.200:3.2"
msgid ""
"Avihesaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto avihesāya cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on compassion, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "an5.200:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ "
"vihesāya;"
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from harming."

msgctxt "an5.200:3.4"
msgid ""
"ye ca vihesāpaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of harming, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "an5.200:3.5"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ vihesāya nissaraṇaṃ. (3)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from harming is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.246"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.200:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno rūpaṃ manasikaroto rūpe cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focuses on form, but their mind isn’t "
"eager …"

msgctxt "an5.200:4.2"
msgid ""
"Arūpaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto arūpe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on the formless, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "an5.200:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ "
"rūpehi;"
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from forms."

msgctxt "an5.200:4.4"
msgid ""
"ye ca rūpapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so taṃ "
"vedanaṃ vediyati."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of form, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "an5.200:4.5"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. (4)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from forms is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.200:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno sakkāyaṃ manasikaroto sakkāye cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take a case where a mendicant focuses on identity, but their mind isn’t "
"eager, confident, settled, and decided about it."

msgctxt "an5.200:5.2"
msgid ""
"Sakkāyanirodhaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ pakkhandati "
"pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"But when they focus on the ending of identity, their mind is eager, "
"confident, settled, and decided about it."

msgctxt "an5.200:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ "
"sakkāyena;"
msgstr ""
"Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and "
"well detached from identity."

msgctxt "an5.200:5.4"
msgid ""
"ye ca sakkāyapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of identity, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "an5.200:5.5"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ sakkāyassa nissaraṇaṃ. (5)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from identity is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: so → idaṃ padaṃ katthaci
msgctxt "an5.200:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa kāmanandīpi nānuseti, byāpādanandīpi nānuseti, vihesānandīpi nānuseti, "
"rūpanandīpi nānuseti, sakkāyanandīpi nānuseti so kāmanandiyāpi ananusayā, "
"byāpādanandiyāpi ananusayā, vihesānandiyāpi ananusayā, rūpanandiyāpi "
"ananusayā, sakkāyanandiyāpi ananusayā."
msgstr ""
"Delight in sensual pleasures, ill will, harming, form, and identity don’t "
"linger within them."

#. VAR: acchecchi → acchejji (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: vivattayi → vāvattayi (bj) | vivaṭṭayi (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.200:6.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu niranusayo, acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi "
"saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassa."
msgstr ""
"That’s why they’re called a mendicant who is without underlying tendencies, "
"who has cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending "
"conceit has made an end of suffering."

msgctxt "an5.200:6.3"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, pañca nissāraṇīyā dhātuyo”ti."
msgstr "These are the five elements of escape.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.200:6.4"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.200:6.5"
msgid "Brāhmaṇavaggo pañcamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.247"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.200:7.1"
msgid "Soṇo doṇo saṅgāravo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.200:7.2"
msgid "Kāraṇapālī ca piṅgiyānī;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.200:7.3"
msgid "Supinā ca vassā vācā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.200:7.4"
msgid "Kulaṃ nissāraṇīyena cāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "an5.200:7.5"
msgid "Catuttho paṇṇāsako samatto."
msgstr ""
